highlights.description: Jean makes the points that our issues are global.
Frustration about resources going to more MTA cops and ads about folks jumping fairs, but not having a library in every community.
There's visible progress with high rises and luxury apartments, but it's hard to see actions being taken for schools and libraries.
Holly, from Brooklyn, NY, shares that as a queer person she is grateful to sometimes be surprised where she finds kinship and community - recently with a bunch of her husband's law colleagues
Information on how the LVN and NYPL partnership came about.

title: Grand Central Conversation - Transit, The Future of NY and Education
